{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"]]},"kind":"article","topicSections":[{"title":"Core Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachine"],"anchor":"Core-Types"},{"title":"Configuration","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineConfiguration","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode"],"anchor":"Configuration"},{"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"API Collection","role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GUI app or the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","isActive":true},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Spooktacular.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}]},{"text":" button or press ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","text":"Managing VMs","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","level":3,"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ssh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}]},{"text":"EC2 Mac Setup","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifie